[ANALYSIS]
The experiment `bow_advanced_20260421_212820_run_01` successfully executed with a BoW (Bag of Words) advanced architecture, achieving an F1 score of 0.7546 and accuracy of 0.8. The model utilized a combination of character n-grams ranging from 4 to 6 and word n-grams up to 3, along with logistic regression regularization parameter `C` set to 3.0. The feature extraction parameters, such as `char_max_features` and `word_max_features`, were reasonably high, which likely contributed to the model's ability to capture complex patterns in the data.

